nt-of-view-matters-scourge-of.html%3Fm%3D1&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE1%2FMFbVPULjdiAdi6tpyrPMY%3D&h=c416d57b\" target=\"_blank\">http://urbankchoze.blogspot.com/2015/08/point-of-view-matters-scourge-of.html?m=1</a><br />\n出名嘅例如 Jan Gehl 應該都有講呢啲"},{"pid":"0116abef2784dc7b2c4706ff7213a8be48ea6eaf","tid":2328752,"uid":26506,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"a319348093582300606877c54f01e13cc96f7d4f","tid":2328752,"uid":26506,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9ab7815fe125d44886eb0dfda13b798d0e93bbf4","tid":2328752,"uid":161781,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"917b912bb71b014e2a980c98bf056916901b3499","tid":2328752,"uid":26506,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-17T23:02:18.000Z","msg":"一定冇 Brasilia ，天上面望落去就好似靚，街上就格格不入，要揸車，唔方便行路"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-18T05:32:26.000Z","msg":"咁樓主係問靚唔靚喎"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-18T05:42:11.000Z","msg":"噉你睇佢嗰陣係淨係喺天上睇或者睇模型？<br />\n地面睇都靚先全面，啫係歐洲可能高處望落好悶，但街景夠美觀；獨裁國家建設可能好狀觀，但去到就唔夠人性同合規模，睇得唔望得<br />\n簡單同非專業講：<a href=\"http://urbankchoze.blogspot.com/2015/08/point-of-view-matters-scourge-of.html?m=1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Furbankchoze.blogspot.com%2F2015%2F08%2Fpoint-of-view-matters-scourge-of.html%3Fm%3D1&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE1%2FMFbVPULjdiAdi6tpyrPMY%3D&h=c416d57b\" target=\"_blank\">http://urbankchoze.blogspot.com/2015/08/point-of-view-matters-scourge-of.html?m=1</a><br />\n出名嘅例如 Jan Gehl 應該都有講呢啲"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-18T05:46:46.000Z","msg":"[edit] <br />\n'Bird Shit Architecture' in Brasilia and Beyond<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hnq1SvmZUYU\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dhnq1SvmZUYU&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE1%2FMFbVPULjdiAdi6tpyrPMY%3D&h=4160ea94\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hnq1SvmZUYU</a><br />\n<br />\nJan Gehl, architect, urban planner, and author of Cities for People, discusses what he calls &quot;bird shit architecture,&quot; a trend in urban planning that originated in the 1950's and persists to the present day. This type of architecture, he explains, is designed to look good from a plane, but not practical for the actual residents of a city.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n-----<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAn important paradigm change happened around 1960. City planning, as a concept, took off on a huge scale in response to the challenge of fast-growing cities. At the same time, traffic planning took over the planning at eye level to address the rapid influx of cars. In the rough and tumble of all this, caring for the people who use cities was completely left behind.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBy 1961, people like Jane Jacobs raised her voice about this new situation in her book, The Death and Life of Great American Cities. But, not much happened for three or four decades. The idea of &quot;Cities for People&quot; became an overlooked and forgotten dimension.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is the story told by Jan Gehl in his new book. He describes why looking after people is crucial for the quality of cities in the 21st century, how it can be accomplished and how it is actually done by now in more and more projects in more and more cities. The transformations carried out in such cities as Copenhagen, Melbourne, Sydney, Amman and New York will serve as examples of this new people-oriented direction in planning. - Australian Broadcasting Corporation"},{"pid":"736410408fdce9edf1c59037cbae5532a75aa26b","tid":2328752,"uid":200317,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f299268d5a63620ccace3c6ea7d48f9e1cdb279f","tid":2328752,"uid":297859,"like":29,"dislike":17,"score":12,"citedBy":5,"replyTime":"2020-12-16T19:54:28.000Z","msg":"講真香港<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n市區極度方便<br />\n又有山有海有外島<br />\n就算住所謂郊區新市填但同住市區無分別<br />\n好多國家市中心外嘅郊區每個區都係擺一個大shopping center 算數<br />\n香港新市鎮仲可以有LV買<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"repl